<font color="#FF0000">WAIT AND SEE</font><br>
<tt>Sun Aug 10  1:17:11 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Arthur:  I am concerned.  When I opted for a different approach to Doc Spatz, I knew that some would be pleased and others dismayed.<br><br>
I have not betrayed you or anyone who has pride in their combat service or who is angered by rhetoric from those who protested and demean our sacrifice.<br><br>
I have conquered my contempt for Doc Spatz... so that I can better focus my contempt upon his views... or lessen my contempt through deeper understanding.  The battle lines are drawn.  He is as adamant (for some reasons) as you and I (for some reasons).  Perhaps, Doc will buy into some of our reasons and justifications, maybe not.  Maybe, we will see him a little differently and at least contemplate where he is coming from.  He has taken a very hard stand and has suffered for it... he has suffered a lot of scorn... perhaps shame and doubt... who knows, besides him.  How are we going to find out if both parties are not at least a little bit vulnerable (it takes courage.)<br><br>
You are more important to me than all the philosophies, arguments, deeds, theories etc... in the world.  I respect your anger and tenacity.<br><br>
I concur that you are an intelligent and sensitive man.  I gain strength from your struggles... and valuable thoughts from your words.<br><br>
Doc Spatz and I have not sold out to either side.  As a matter of fact, the war has just begun.  Hopefully, some good revelations will come from the battles yet to be fought.<br><br>
With deep respect and mild concern,<br><br>
Ed
